post_text: Good morning! Please start watching your mail for an EBT food card that the state of Oklahoma has granted to each child at Stuart school, since we feed all children for free. In the past, only children who qualified for free or reduced meals qualified for this benefit. We received the information this morning and are putting it on our school website and Facebook page. The card will probably come mailed in your child's name and be in a plain looking envelope. There are instructions included that will tell you how to activate the card. If you do not receive one for each child, use the information on the website to contact the state. Hope you have a blessed day!

post_text: Just a reminder that we have moved the start date of school to Thursday August 20th. If at all possible, we ask that you bring your child to school.If not, we will maintain social distancing and students will wear a mask on the bus. Kiamichi Technology Center begins classes tomorrow, August 12th. The Career Tech bus will be by our school at 7:40 a.m. and return about 11:40 a.m. KTC strongly encourages students to begin class tomorrow even if the home school isn't in session. Instead of coming to the school, students may either drive themselves or have parents drop them off at KTC. KTC requires students to wear a mask on the bus and on their campus. Sophomore and Junior enrolment are Monday August 17 from 9a.m. until 2p.m.

post_text: Stuart public schools had an employee test positive for covid-19 today. This employee was at physicals Monday and at Enrollment Tuesday evening. We are canceling enrollment for this evening and tomorrow, as well as all athletic events for the remainder of this week, with next week's activities to be determined at a later time. The possibility of students being infected was very minimal as they did not spend enough time nor were they in close contact with the person. We are simply letting everyone know and taking precautions to make sure we keep our school family safe and healthy. It is in everyone's best interest to take temperature checks daily and monitor yourselves and your children for any other symptoms.

post_text: Next week, May 11th through 15th, is our last scheduled week of school. On Tuesday, May 12th through Thursday May 14th, there will be a Dropbox outside so all packet work can be dropped off. Also, Friday, May 15th will be our last day to deliver meals. Grade cards will be mailed out the following week. If senior transcripts or diplomas are needed before the graduation ceremony, please contact the school to set up a time to pick them up. There is someone in the office on Monday, Tuesday, and Thursday from 8 a.m. until 3 pm. Each graduating senior and 8th grader will be mailed 10 tickets for family to come to the graduation ceremony. All information about graduation is posted on our website and Facebook page. Thank you and stay healthy!

post_text: Since the public libraries are closed and checking out a physical book isn’t possible, here is an alternative. The Internet Archive website https://archive.org/ has over 20 million of downloadable books and texts available for free. There is also a collection of over a million modern e-books that can be borrowed by anyone with a free archive.org account. You can create an account at https://archive.org/account/login and borrow a book for 14 days. You may read the books online in your browser or download them into Adobe Digital Editions, which is a software program used for reading e-books on a variety of different devices. For more information, go to the FAQ page that is available at https://help.archive.org/hc/en-us.

post_text: Beginning this Friday, April 3rd, grades pre-k through four, along with students for all other grades who do not have connectivity to the internet or a device to do online work will need to pick up student work from 8 a.m. until 2 pm. We ask that you drive up and we will bring out their work. Please stay in your vehicles and stay in line. We are allowing no entrance into the school to protect our cafeteria staff who are providing meals for students. We are only giving work at this time. Upon the CDC giving the all clear, we will choose a date this summer for people to come get their child's belongings from their classroom or locker and we will schedule prom and graduation ceremonies at that time. Thank you for your cooperation and all of your prayers!

post_text: Good afternoon. After watching the press conference with Governor Stitt yesterday and sitting in a webinar with the State Superintendent of Public Instruction today, it is suggested that we do not cancel school unless the Coronavirus spreads through community transmission. Community transmission is defined as "two people in areas of 800,000 have coronavirus that are not connected to travel or through personal contact with a known case." (This is roughly the population of Tulsa.) Please look at our website or at the CDC website and follow the guidelines for travel. It will tell who must self quarantine upon return and places where travel is restricted. If you plan on traveling outside our state or country on spring break, please look at those guidelines carefully. It is still determined that keeping your hands clean, maintaining social distance from others, and the cleaning surfaces with disinfectant are the best ways to prevent the spread of this virus. Thank you for your time and I hope you all have a wonderful spring break!
text: Good afternoon. After watching the press conference with Governor Stitt yesterday and sitting in a webinar with the State Superintendent of Public Instruction today, it is suggested that we do not cancel school unless the Coronavirus spreads through community transmission. Community transmission is defined as "two people in areas of 800,000 have coronavirus that are not connected to travel or through personal contact with a known case." (This is roughly the population of Tulsa.) Please look at our website or at the CDC website and follow the guidelines for travel. It will tell who must self quarantine upon return and places where travel is restricted. If you plan on traveling outside our state or country on spring break, please look at those guidelines carefully. It is still determined that keeping your hands clean, maintaining social distance from others, and the cleaning surfaces with disinfectant are the best ways to prevent the spread of this virus. Thank you for your time and I hope you all have a wonderful spring break!

post_text:
A little after 1pm today, Governor Stitt, State Superintendent Hoffmeister, the head of the Ok Health Department and a Dr. from the medical Board gave a press conference. You can see it by typing the following in your web browser. rdm.me/MgxoZsf68l
They said to continue school and continue working, just use normal precautions such as keeping 6 ft away from others, washing hands regularly, drinking plenty of water and covering sneezes and coughs. You should refrain from shaking hands and other close personal contact. Again, we are upping our efforts to sanitize water fountains, door knobs, restrooms, computers and desks. If your child has a fever, we ask that you keep them home as you would with any other virus. Thank you in advance for your cooperation.

They said to continue school and continue working, just use normal precautions such as keeping 6 ft away from others, washing hands regularly, drinking plenty of water and covering sneezes and coughs. You should refrain from shaking hands and other close personal contact. Again, we are upping our efforts to sanitize water fountains, door knobs, restrooms, computers and desks. If your child has a fever, we ask that you keep them home as you would with any other virus. Thank you in advance for your cooperation.

*avoid close contact
*cover that cough or sneeze

post_text:
PLEASE SHARE TO GET THE WORD OUT:

Our 2018 Stuart Alumni Dinner will be on Saturday, May 12th from 6-9p.m.
This year we will be honoring graduates from years ending in "8". The dinner price is $15.
Our menu includes Roast Beef, Mashed Potatoes & Gravy, Green Beans, Hot Rolls, Salad/Fruit Bar, & Cobbler w/ice cream!
You may send in your reservations early, or pay at the door.
As always we have a BEAUTIFUL Quilt to auction off to benefit the Stuart Alumni Scholarship Fund which was lovingly made by our Stuart Stitch & Sew ladies. We also hope to have live entertainment showcasing some amazing local talent before the meal.

You can mail your reservations to:
Stuart School Alumni Committee
8837 4th Street
Stuart, Ok 74570
Or call: 918-546-2627 ext.100 for more information.

Many heartfelt thanks to all Alumni who attend our annual dinners! Your attendance helps to provide scholarships for Stuart Seniors each year! We appreciate you for continuing to support our students and our school!

post_text: Attention all current Kg-3rd Grade parents. Applications for Choctaw Summer Reading Program are being sent home this week. This year's theme is Super Heroes in training. Our students who attended regularly last summer showed great improvement in Reading. Please send those applications back by Wednesday, April 25th to ensure a spot is reserved for your child. Summer school will run from May 29th through June 29th. There will be a professional day with no school on June 1st.

post_text: Due to the outpouring of love and support for Shannon, Ashley, and Justin, many people have been asking about bringing food and meals for them in the next few weeks. In order to try to help organize the food donations, we are starting a food sign up calendar at Stuart School where anyone interested in helping out may call in to find out what days are open to bring food for the family. If you are interested in bringing any food items for the Brown family you may contact Stuart School @ 918-546-2627 ext.100 to find out what days are available and what items are needed. Calls can be made from 8a.m. to 3p.m. Monday through Thursday . Please share and tag this message so everyone who may wish to participate can see this post. Words cannot express how amazing it is to be part of such an awesome community and school family who love and care for each other so much! God bless!

April 16, 2017 at 6:24 PM ·

This coming week is our big push for registrations. Race day is less than 2 weeks away and the t-shirt order has to go in next weekend. The pre-registration deadline is this coming Friday, April 21st. This is the cut-off to ensure you will receive your preferred t-shirt size. Every early registration helps with planning and budgeting for the event so we are encouraging everyone to sign up as early as possible. Click the link to register today http://hornethustle.org/
